items.description:
The LoRA inspired from the Japanese Fashion Designer by Yohji Yamamoto.

recommended weights 0,8 - 0,9.

Hey there, apologies for any inconvenience caused! Just a heads up, the LoRA model can also generate an Asian face, but we understand that it might not be everyone's cup of tea. If you're one of those users who prefer to see something different, try using the negative prompt and typing in 'asian' or 'asian face' to explore other options. Hope that helps! Let us know if you have any other questions.

items.name: Aphrodite
items.description:
Aphrodite from Hercules.

Trained on 3250 steps.

You may have to work some to get good images. But it's pretty good and on-model 90% of the time.

You want to include "1girl, (colored_skin:1.5), dress, strapless, purple_skin, solo, blonde hair, breasts, long hair, lipstick, blue eyes, cartoon, (flat color)," In your prompt. As these bring out the most of the Lora.

items.name: Second Life (Anime Version)
items.description:
This is a Lora that tries to mimic Second life in-game screenshots. It has mostly been trained on anime style avatars, the environment and objects. It works best at 0.8~1. For best results use UNIPC sampler and add "3DCG, polygon rendering" in the positive prompt and "2d drawing" in the negative prompt. "Pretty face" or "pretty eyes" in the prompt also seem to give better face results with authentic in-game look. Perhaps there are other prompts I am not aware of to make it seem less like a CGI prerendering or drawing. Doing a hires fix with latent upscale seems to fix eyes and disfigured body.

I was able to make some furries and human avatars as well (the word 'cat' seems to be the triggerword for furries, and mature male/female for humans)

items.name: Prompt weighting interpretations for ComfyUI
items.description:
Contains a node that lets you set how ComfyUI should interpret up/down-weighted tokens. By default ComfyUI does not interpret prompt weighting the same way as A1111 does. This node lets you switch between different ways in which this is done in frameworks such as ComfyUI, A1111 and compel. It also includes a node that let's you mix CLIP embeddings for some additional customization.

For a detailed explanation of the methods, the introduced nodes, or raise an issue, please see the github page for this project.

items.name: Belly Dance Dress
items.description:
Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

Training settings:

35 images, 25 steps, 10 epochs, you find many epochs (with test images using plot xy script) on my Patreon while supporting me.


Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras (Recommended for best quality, you may try other samplers)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9

  • LORA weight for txt2img: reccomended 0.4-0.7

  • Keys: wearing belly dance dress, dancing

  • Adviced Image Size: 512x768

This model has been trained on images without background, it was my first time doing this and i discovered it is a bit problematic to generate the background you want.

My advice is to start your prompt with "a woman wearing belly dance dress" with a weight of the model of atleast 0.4, adviced 0.5 but it may give better results in the dress design till 0.8.

Then put a big weight to the kind of background you want, atleast 1.3. or as you will see in many of the images i posted with the model, you will get an empty background.

After this experience i strongly advice to always use images with background for LORA model trainings.

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

Other versions

A LoRA based on 4267 Grimoire A: Private Grimoire Magic Academy cards, recognizing 60+ characters to varying degrees.

A request by Civit user themonky007. The model is far from complete but there are currently no plans to further improve it. The dataset is available for those willing to take on the task.

Lesson of the day: suitable learning rates can differ significantly between datasets (this uses 2e-4 while the Idolmaster models use 1e-3).

An undertrained version (v0.1) with card text is also available. Unlike v1.0, v0.1 uses Japanese names with spaces (e.g. æœæ¯”å¥ˆ é¾å­£) as character tags. Interestingly, it can produce the correct Romaji initials for out-of-distribution characters quite reliably.

Dataset:

  • 4267 Grimoire cards extracted from official offline apps with text removed (characters labeled by themonky007)

Tags generated with SmilingWolf/wd-v1-4-convnextv2-tagger-v2 with a threshold of 0.35. No balancing and tag cleaning. Images were processed with RealESRGAN_x4plus_anime_6B.

Inspired by a 2022 paper, a custom LR scheduler was used:

SequentialLR(optimizer, [
    LinearLR(optimizer, 0.1, total_iters=steps_per_epoch),
    CosineAnnealingWarmRestarts(optimizer, steps_per_epoch*2, T_mult=2)
], [steps_per_epoch])

items.name: Subaru Impreza Second generation First facelift
items.description:
https://t.me/stdif_kos

After mixed reaction to the round headlight design, in 2001 Subaru enlisted the help of Peter Stevens of Prodrive, who updated the car's fascia in 2002 (2003 in the US for the 2004 model year), with more rectangular headlamps. For the US market, the facelifted Impreza was offered as 2.5 RS Sedan and TS Wagon, 2.5 Outback Sport Wagon, WRX Sedan and Wagon, and the new WRX STI Sedan. Sport Package was optional for the RS, and the WRX could be ordered with Premium Package. The RS, TS, Outback Sport, and WRX are available with manual or automatic transmission, while the sole transmission for the STI is 6-speed manual. This version of the Impreza has gained the nickname 'Blob Eye' among Subaru enthusiasts.

In 2005, Subaru made their AVCS standard on all engines used in the Impreza.

From June 2005 in Japan (2006 model year) Imprezas have been redesigned, along with new headlights, taillights, and bumpers. items.name: Arthur Morgan
items.description:
Arthur Morgan was born circa 1863 to Beatrice and Lyle Morgan in the northern US. As a child, his mother died of unknown causes, while his father was a petty criminal and outlaw. In 1874, when Arthur was 11 years old, his father was arrested for larceny. Morgan later witnessed his death and, despite a strained relationship with him, still donned his hat and kept a picture of him.

Around 1877, Arthur was found as a 'wild delinquent' and picked up off the streets by Dutch van der Linde and Hosea Matthews.[4] Viewing the pair as surrogate father figures, Arthur came to share Dutch's vision of a life lived free from the constraints of civilization and the rule of law. The pair taught him how to read, write, hunt, fight, shoot, and ride, becoming their first protÃ©gÃ© as well as one of the founding members of the Van der Linde gang.

A@B:~/bulk-image-cropper$ pip install flask

A@B:~/bulk-image-cropper$ python app.py

Access via 127.0.0.1:5000

I only added a app.py python file to host it on your local PC, all credit goes to https://github.com/danfickle/bulk-image-cropper

  • It is not overfitted (previous version was overfitted due to small dataset and many 3D blender images);

  • Smaller filesize.

  • Tokens were reworked manually in Dataset tag editor for easy prompting. So read new tokens for better experience.

Main info:

Trained on animefull;

0.8-1 is the best radius.

Clip skip 2.

Tokens for prompt:

Main appearance:

Luluffx, mature female, 1girl,

black hair, single hair bun, hair over one eye, one eye covered, lipstick, makeup, purple necklace;

optional: braid;

Default dress:

off-shoulder dress, black dress, strapless, fur trim, multiple belts, garter straps, thighhighs

Recommended:

curvy, large breasts, cleavage,

perfect eyes, perfect face, detailed face, sweat

Extra info! I recommend you next prompt order for NAI-based mixes (you can see it in my preview arts):

  1. highres, high quality (and masterpiece if it doesn't break character appearence from LoRA). Also other lighting / shadows / sharpness / fov / colorful if you need effects are here. Sometimes it doesn't work if style of anime or game was baked in LoRA.

  2. Activation word (from lora civitai page, usually character name), what character is doing (with details), char expressions, camera position, background;

  3. Hair details, face details, jewelry, crowns, hats, etc.

  4. Clothes and shoes; Or nude, naked.

  5. Body details (large breasts, cleavage). Genitals if you want generate it.

Also LoRA trained with some NSFW poses. So you can try it with LoRAs or without it.

Advices for better upscaling and fixing visual bugs:

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  use highres.fix (If you are sure that your prompt is easy for SD); I prefer x4_Fatal_anime_500000_G, animesharp, foolhardy_remacri, siax with 1.5x - 2x upscale.

Â· use extention after detailer for better faces. It is better than inpaint.

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  use SD Upscale / Ultimate SD Upscale script in img2img;

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Use inpaint and sketch (or Photopea) for other details;

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Use Photoshop / Photopea extension.

I will be glad to receive feedback from you and a demonstration of your art with my LoRA!

For previous versions:

This is NSFW model with mostly open dressed, lingerie and naked variants.

LoRA was trained on Perfect world model with 3D NSFW/SFW arts.

2nd ver was trained on animefill-pruned.ckpt.

Also second alt. version was trained on "vanilla" SD 1.5 for best compitability with realistic models like Deliberate v2.

V1.1 is also good! If you like it more - use it. But it was made without trigger words and more with deepbooru interrogates.

60 arts were used (4000 (2000 with batch size 2) steps with 10 epoches).

0.75-0.9 strength of Lora is the best radius.

Clip skip 2 for anime-based models and clip skip 1 for realistic SD1.5 models.

Some necessary Waifu diffusion prompt for better experience:

LuluFFX, mature female, eyebrows behind hair, hair over one eye, covered eye

black hair, hair stick, hair bun,

For dress:

black dress, strapless, bare shoulders, fur trim.

If you have troubles with distorted eyes or bangs:

  • use highres.fix (I prefer not to do this);

  • use SD Upscale script in img2img (For me 1.25-1.5x with AnimeSharp or UltraSharp is good on 0.2-0.3 denoising strengh);

  • Use inpaint (but with SD Upscale and dddetailer I don't need this in 90% times);

  • Use Photoshop.

I will be glad to receive feedback from you and a demonstration of your art with my LoRA!

items.name: Rolo
items.description:
Rolo Style LoRA

This LoRA model is inspired by the art style of Rolo (@rolo_stuff) and is optimized for use with a weight between 1 and 0.5. If the output appears too overbaked, consider reducing the weight. The model was trained on Anything V3, with a focus on rolo's art style. It works particularly well with tags such as rolo, furry, body fur, tail.

Please note that while this model is not designed specifically for any particular character or subject, it is mostly trained on Rolo's main OC. As with any style model, some output may not perfectly match the desired style, but overall the model produces good results.

Please be aware that this model is not intended to be used to impersonate or steal Rolo's work. It is intended purely for fun and creative experimentation. If you use this model in your designs, please make sure to incorporate creative differences and avoid passing off the output as original work by Rolo.

To use this model in Auto1111:

  1. Update the webui (use git pull or redownload it)

  2. Copy the model file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  3. Select the Rolo Style LoRA in the webui (make sure to include rolo, furry, body fur)

  4. Adjust the weight as needed (default is 1)

Thank you for using my Rolo Style LoRA model! If you have any questions or feedback, please don't hesitate to reach out.

items.name: CHAOS Warrior lora (fantasy)
items.description:
"CHAOS could be here" he thought, "I've never been in these wastes before. There could be CHAOS anywhere." The cool winds of magic felt good against his bare chest. "I HATE CHAOS" he thought. Where have all the gobbos gone reverberated his entire steam tank, making it pulsate even as the 9 gelt bugman's circulated through his powerful Solland veins and washed away his (merited) fear of ratmen after dark. "With a steam tank, you can go anywhere you want" he said to himself, out loud.

This lora generates chaos warriors and was trained in a booru tag style. Can do undivided or monogod (khorne, tzeentch, nurgle, slaanesh) and also chaos sorcerers. Seems to work best with AnythingV4.5 which has the side effect of making it pretty compatible with anime and memes.

This is a lazy first draft, trained on a dirty dataset of about 150 images. Including a significant amount of T-posing total war models so i recommend you put "reference pose" in negative prompts.
